# Static archive of GameCon 2002 (reconstructed from the Internet Archive).
#
# GameCon 2002 was SPECIAL — it ran as part of Avalcon/Eurocon in CHOTĚBOŘ
# (not the usual Olomouc; the European SF/F/horror meet). It was run by the
# Altar publishing house, and in 2002 GameCon was a SECTION of the whole
# altar.cz publisher site (path altar.cz/gamecon/) — the same path-era as
# 2003-2005, older than the gamecon.altar.cz subdomain (2006-2008).
#
# Scope: the GameCon pages (homepage, mistrovství, přihláška, the tournament
# pages, and the Mistrovství v DrD results archive vysledky98..02) served at the
# root, PLUS the Altar publisher-site nav menu it links to (section landing
# pages, fetched from the 2002 capture window). All restored from
# web.archive.org, transcoded WINDOWS-1250 -> UTF-8 (with an injected
# <meta charset>, since the source declared charset only via the HTTP header).
#
# The Avalcon special page (www.avalcon.cz) was a SEPARATE domain (the combined
# con's own site) — now dead, left as a captured external link. Dynamic CGI
# (/cgi/*), the catalog, and uncaptured pages fall to the themed 404. Assets
# (stylesheets/default.css, img/*) are served at their original absolute paths.

DirectoryIndex index.html
ErrorDocument 404 /404.html

# No directory listings — an orphaned dir should fall to the themed 404.
Options -Indexes

<IfModule mod_rewrite.c>
    RewriteEngine On

    # Serve real files directly (pages at root, assets under their paths).
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -f
    RewriteRule ^ - [L]

    # Serve a real directory only if it has an index.html; else themed 404.
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -d
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME}/index.html -f
    RewriteRule ^ - [L]

    # Homepage.
    RewriteRule ^$  index.html [L]

    # Everything else (cross-site Altar chrome, uncaptured) -> themed 404.
    RewriteRule ^.*$ - [R=404,L]
</IfModule>
